01:23:40.946 --> 01:23:43.501
taught him how to bob and weave.

1301
01:23:43.535 --> 01:23:44.916
size up his opponents.

1302
01:23:44.950 --> 01:23:47.815
anticipating their next move.

1303
01:23:47.850 --> 01:23:50.025
put an edge on his strategic approach.

1304
01:23:52.096 --> 01:23:56.065
Now. he stared
at his map for the hundredth time.

1305
01:23:56.100 --> 01:24:00.483
Every single block in Chinatown
had had a confirmed case.

1306
01:24:03.383 --> 01:24:05.764
But in the previous September.

1307
01:24:05.799 --> 01:24:08.560
a white washerwoman with
no connection to the district

1308
01:24:08.595 --> 01:24:12.771
had died of plague.
and she lived a block away.

1309
01:24:15.326 --> 01:24:18.156
It dawned on Blue
he'd been ignoring something

1310
01:24:18.191 --> 01:24:21.194
that had been right in front
of him the entire time.

1311
01:24:23.851 --> 01:24:26.095
The mystery of why the plague

1312
01:24:26.130 --> 01:24:28.753
had decimated Europe
and Asia for centuries

1313
01:24:28.787 --> 01:24:32.170
was finally beginning to unravel.

1314
01:24:36.830 --> 01:24:39.315
For us kids.

1315
01:24:39.350 --> 01:24:42.456
one of the great pastimes was
just fishing off

1316
01:24:42.491 --> 01:24:47.323
the piers. which ran almost
right up against Chinatown.

1317
01:24:48.566 --> 01:24:51.500
And ships that were moored to the docks.

1318
01:24:51.534 --> 01:24:53.260
they had these huge ropes.

1319
01:24:55.159 --> 01:24:57.022
You would see rats.

1320
01:24:57.057 --> 01:24:58.679
Rats just coming from the ships

1321
01:24:58.714 --> 01:25:00.336
and coming down those ropes.

1322
01:25:02.062 --> 01:25:04.133
And some of them would just fall
in the water.

1323
01:25:04.168 --> 01:25:07.102
Others were able to find their
way onto the docks.

1324
01:25:08.862 --> 01:25:12.210
They scurried. they were fast.
and they were quick.

1325
01:25:20.115 --> 01:25:22.358
Rats are biological marvels in many ways

1326
01:25:22.393 --> 01:25:24.636
because they can survive almost anything.

1327
01:25:24.671 --> 01:25:27.225
And they can breed incredibly quickly.

1328
01:25:28.916 --> 01:25:31.643
And a single pair of rats.

1329
01:25:31.678 --> 01:25:34.198
left to reproduce unhampered.

1330
01:25:34.232 --> 01:25:38.478
would become 1.500 in a year.

1331
01:25:41.791 --> 01:25:46.244
In his lab. Blue and his
men had discovered plague germs

1332
01:25:46.279 --> 01:25:50.179
in dead rats that they had dissected.

1333
01:25:50.214 --> 01:25:52.940
He was now struck by the possibility

1334
01:25:52.975 --> 01:25:56.358
that rats themselves
might somehow spread the disease

1335
01:25:56.392 --> 01:25:59.292
as they roamed the city.

1336
01:25:59.326 --> 01:26:01.949
though he still had no idea how.

1337
01:26:04.055 --> 01:26:05.815
And he realizes

1338
01:26:05.850 --> 01:26:07.783
the only way we're going
to save San Francisco

1339
01:26:07.817 --> 01:26:09.750
is if we kill as many rats as possible.

1340
01:26:09.785 --> 01:26:12.995
So. they focus on rat eradication.

1341
01:26:16.136 --> 01:26:19.070
Thanks to Wong Chung's prior outreach.

1342
01:26:19.104 --> 01:26:21.486
the Chinese Six Companies now agreed

1343
01:26:21.521 --> 01:26:23.385
