01:37:07.994 --> 01:37:11.170
There was a physician who had perceived

1513
01:37:11.204 --> 01:37:14.414
a bad smell in his house.

1514
01:37:14.449 --> 01:37:17.797
The doctor decided he would chop
out a hole in the wall

1515
01:37:17.832 --> 01:37:21.283
and get to the source
of this unpleasant odor.

1516
01:37:21.318 --> 01:37:24.597
And there he found two dead rats.

1517
01:37:24.631 --> 01:37:28.601
And immediately. two members
of the family got the plague.

1518
01:37:31.742 --> 01:37:35.263
As Blue pondered the details of this case.

1519
01:37:35.297 --> 01:37:36.954
he recalled reading a recent report

1520
01:37:36.989 --> 01:37:39.094
from the British Plague Commission

1521
01:37:39.129 --> 01:37:41.545
that confirmed the results of a study

1522
01:37:41.579 --> 01:37:43.547
completed ten years earlier.

1523
01:37:46.446 --> 01:37:49.104
Pasteur Institute scientist

1524
01:37:49.139 --> 01:37:50.899
Paul Louis Simond did this experiment.

1525
01:37:50.934 --> 01:37:55.490
He put two rats in cages side
by side. separated by a grate.

1526
01:37:55.524 --> 01:37:57.147
They couldn't touch one another.

1527
01:37:57.181 --> 01:38:00.115
One rat was healthy. one rat was
sick with the plague.

1528
01:38:00.150 --> 01:38:03.360
And Simond made
the breakthrough observation

1529
01:38:03.394 --> 01:38:05.603
that when the plague rat died.

1530
01:38:05.638 --> 01:38:08.572
the fleas jumped to the side
of the healthy rat

1531
01:38:08.606 --> 01:38:10.470
for their next blood meal.

1532
01:38:12.231 --> 01:38:16.131
Bubonic plague
is transmitted by Yersinia pestis.

1533
01:38:16.166 --> 01:38:21.516
The flea itself is really
the host of Yersinia pestis.

1534
01:38:21.550 --> 01:38:25.658
And when it seeks a blood meal
on its natural host.

1535
01:38:25.692 --> 01:38:27.902
it regurgitates its bacteria

1536
01:38:27.936 --> 01:38:30.559
and transmits plague.

1537
01:38:33.114 --> 01:38:36.393
And it's only when its own host dies.

1538
01:38:36.427 --> 01:38:37.704
the flea seeks another warm body.

1539
01:38:37.739 --> 01:38:44.366
a rat. or if a human comes by.
they'll jump on.

1540
01:38:44.401 --> 01:38:47.231
It senses that there's something
warm here.

1541
01:38:47.266 --> 01:38:48.232
"I don't care what it is."

1542
01:38:50.303 --> 01:38:51.615
And then they'll bite.

1543
01:38:51.649 --> 01:38:55.239
They'll try to feed. because it's hungry.

1544
01:38:55.274 --> 01:38:56.965
So. the cause of the transmission

1545
01:38:57.000 --> 01:38:59.726
between rats and human was the flea.

1546
01:39:02.074 --> 01:39:03.834
Blue was thunderstruck

1547
01:39:03.868 --> 01:39:05.180
by the realization

1548
01:39:05.215 --> 01:39:07.355
that fleas played the primary role

1549
01:39:07.389 --> 01:39:08.804
in transmitting the disease.

1550
01:39:11.083 --> 01:39:15.742
Rats. he now understood.
were only agents of the epidemic

1551
01:39:15.777 --> 01:39:19.505
because of the insects in their fur.

1552
01:39:19.539 --> 01:39:22.301
And pieces fell into place:

1553
01:39:22.335 --> 01:39:24.544
the peaks of the outbreak lined up

1554
01:39:24.579 --> 01:39:27.099
with the flea's active season.

1555
01:39:27.133 --> 01:39:33.139
The baffling on-again. off-again
pattern became crystal clear.

1556
01:39:33.174 --> 01:39:36.625
So. the bubonic plague bacilla

1557
01:39:36.660 --> 01:39:39.974
was best conveyed by fleas
on rats biting humans.

1558
01:39:41.182 --> 01:39:45.358
That transmission was the most
important thing.

1559
01:39:45.393 --> 01:39:49.086
So. the eradication of rats
would be pretty significant.

1560
01:39:51.744 --> 01:39:54.712
As the city continued to rebuild.

1561
01:39:54.747 --> 01:39:59.131
Blue knew that public support
for rat extermination was solid.

1562
01:40:00.546 --> 01:40:05.413
Still. without full buy-in
from the entire community.

1563
01:40:05.447 --> 01:40:09.175
the stream of rats
would continue unchecked.

1564
01:40:09.210 --> 01:40:12.661
It was time for extreme measures.

1565
01:40:12.696 --> 01:40:14.870
Rupert Blue the strategist

1566
01:40:14.905 --> 01:40:16.907
understood he needed both
a carrot and a stick.

1567
01:40:16.941 --> 01:40:20.600
So fleet week was approaching.

1568
01:40:20.635 --> 01:40:26.365
But Blue told the city. if the
city isn't a healthful place.

1569
01:40:26.399 --> 01:40:31.577
I will tell the admiral that
it's not safe to land his ships.

1570
01:40:31.611 --> 01:40:35.339
This was terrible news.

1571
01:40:35.374 --> 01:40:37.755
It would be like canceling Christmas.

1572
01:40:37.790 --> 01:40:40.793
to have the Great White Fleet barred

1573
01:40:40.827 --> 01:40:43.278
from entering San Francisco. and worse yet

1574
01:40:43.313 --> 01:40:46.074
diverted to Seattle. the rival city.

1575
01:40:46.109 --> 01:40:48.007
would have been terrible.

1576
01:40:48.042 --> 01:40:52.598
So. all the city had to take part.

1577
01:40:54.358 --> 01:40:58.500
In 1908. the first truly grassroots.

1578
01:40:58.535 --> 01:41:04.092
fully public. multi-sector
health campaign was born.

1579
01:41:04.127 --> 01:41:06.957
Educating the populace on simple things

1580
01:41:06.991 --> 01:41:10.202
like the right way to dispose of garbage.

1581
01:41:11.962 --> 01:41:15.897
You have to seal your household
and security against rats.

1582
01:41:15.931 --> 01:41:18.382
They also educated greengrocers
on the right way

1583
01:41:18.417 --> 01:41:20.315
to store their wares

1584
01:41:20.350 --> 01:41:22.110
to keep the city streets clean.

1585
01:41:22.145 --> 01:41:27.011
And they informed essential
nature of sanitary precautions.

1586
01:41:28.737 --> 01:41:31.292
They start putting
notices in everybody's mailboxes.

1587
01:41:31.326 --> 01:41:36.331
Like. this is what you can do to
save yourself and save the city.

1588
01:41:36.366 --> 01:41:39.023
And little by little.

1589
01:41:39.058 --> 01:41:41.060
hundreds and hundreds of citizens

1590
01:41:41.095 --> 01:41:43.131
from all walks of life.

1591
01:41:43.166 --> 01:41:44.305
churches.

1592
01:41:44.339 --> 01:41:46.824
temples. lodges.

1593
01:41:46.859 --> 01:41:50.034
women's clubs. business groups.

1594
01:41:50.069 --> 01:41:52.244
everyone got on board and did their part.

1595
01:41:55.523 --> 01:41:57.628
San Francisco got to work.

1596
01:41:57.663 --> 01:42:02.461
Long-neglected sanitary
infrastructure was rebuilt.

1597
01:42:02.495 --> 01:42:07.949
A $4 million bond was issued
to renovate the sewer system.

1598
01:42:07.983 --> 01:42:12.333
and municipal garbage collection
and disposal were put in place.

1599
01:42:14.749 --> 01:42:17.476
By now. even the local newspapers

1600
01:42:17.510 --> 01:42:19.340
supported the sanitation drive

1601
01:42:19.374 --> 01:42:21.273
by publishing the names and addresses

1602
01:42:21.307 --> 01:42:23.413
of anyone who failed to comply.

1603
01:42:25.069 --> 01:42:26.830
In the end.

1604
01:42:26.864 --> 01:42:31.938
Blue managed to have more
than 20.000 houses inspected.

1605
01:42:31.973 --> 01:42:36.115
Untold numbers of rats were
either trapped or found dead.

1606
01:42:36.150 --> 01:42:38.324
But of the ones tested.

1607
01:42:38.359 --> 01:42:41.465
only 16 were found to be infected.

1608
01:42:41.500 --> 01:42:44.434
The outbreak was in retreat.

1609
01:42:46.470 --> 01:42:50.647
With backbreaking work.
and focused messaging.

1610
01:42:50.681 --> 01:42:53.788
Blue had finally rounded
the corner on the disease.

1611
01:43:04.281 --> 01:43:07.526
The question that had so long
tormented Kinyoun and Blue...

1612
01:43:07.560 --> 01:43:11.081
why hadn't the plague taken off
exponentially?

1613
01:43:11.115 --> 01:43:13.325
was at last answered.

1614
01:43:17.570 --> 01:43:22.057
It's so interesting that we had the germ

1615
01:43:22.092 --> 01:43:25.647
that was just as lethal
as during the Black Death.

1616
01:43:25.682 --> 01:43:30.169
The same germ that had ravaged
populations in China.

1617
01:43:30.204 --> 01:43:35.243
and India. what may have
saved the city in the end

1618
01:43:35.278 --> 01:43:37.487
from a much worse disaster

1619
01:43:37.521 --> 01:43:41.387
was a tiny part of an organ
inside of the little flea.

1620
01:43:43.527 --> 01:43:46.220
In places where you
had this explosion of plague.

1621
01:43:46.254 --> 01:43:48.912
there was a different species of rat flea.

1622
01:43:48.946 --> 01:43:51.501
Its anatomy was slightly different.

1623
01:43:51.535 --> 01:43:53.123
It would inject more of the plague bacilli

1624
01:43:53.157 --> 01:43:56.713
into whatever victim it bit.

1625
01:43:56.747 --> 01:44:01.718
In San Francisco. the flea bite
would inject a lower dose.

1626
01:44:01.752 --> 01:44:05.342
harder for it to become
a full-blown disease.

1627
01:44:06.826 --> 01:44:12.004
So. it was only this quirk of flea anatomy

1628
01:44:12.038 --> 01:44:14.040
that really prevented millions
of deaths in the U.S.

1629
01:44:17.458 --> 01:44:21.600
February 1908 saw the last diagnosed case

1630
01:44:21.634 --> 01:44:24.050
of bubonic plague.

1631
01:44:24.085 --> 01:44:26.605
For the first time in nearly eight years.

1632
01:44:26.639 --> 01:44:29.573
San Francisco could afford to celebrate.

1633
01:44:29.608 --> 01:44:31.679
And on May 6. 1908.

1634
01:44:31.713 --> 01:44:35.510
the Great White Fleet
sailed into San Francisco Bay.

1635
01:44:46.280 --> 01:44:48.696
People stood atop
every hill and promontory

1636
01:44:48.730 --> 01:44:50.111
to get a look at these

1637
01:44:50.145 --> 01:44:52.665
magnificent golden and white ships

1638
01:44:52.700 --> 01:44:54.288
that were sent by Theodore Roosevelt.

1639
01:44:55.841 --> 01:45:01.502
People were waving flags
and partying all week.

1640
01:45:01.536 --> 01:45:03.089
It celebrated not only

1641
01:45:03.124 --> 01:45:05.747
the Great White Fleet
and naval power. but also

1642
01:45:05.782 --> 01:45:08.681
the rebirth of San Francisco
as a healthful city.

1643
01:45:08.716 --> 01:45:12.720
And it was an effort in which
everyone had taken part.

1644
01:45:16.862 --> 01:45:22.074
Chinatown was celebrating its own victory.

1645
01:45:24.041 --> 01:45:26.803
Its near-total destruction
during the earthquake

1646
01:45:26.837 --> 01:45:28.529
had lured white speculators

1647
01:45:28.563 --> 01:45:32.360
eager to snap up the valuable land.

1648
01:45:34.569 --> 01:45:37.365
But they hadn't counted on the
fierce opposition

1649
01:45:37.400 --> 01:45:40.092
of Chinese merchants and associations.

1650
01:45:40.126 --> 01:45:43.371
who fought them tooth and nail

1651
01:45:43.406 --> 01:45:46.581
to control how they wanted
the district to be used.

1652
01:45:50.413 --> 01:45:51.931
We later learn. of course.

1653
01:45:51.966 --> 01:45:55.970
they were quite successful in turning

1654
01:45:56.004 --> 01:45:58.766
the fear of Chinatown

1655
01:45:58.800 --> 01:46:02.390
as a labyrinth of disease and immorality

1656
01:46:02.425 --> 01:46:06.912
into a kind of middle-class.
consumer tourist paradise.

1657
01:46:13.505 --> 01:46:17.198
On March 31. 1909.

1658
01:46:17.232 --> 01:46:20.339
Rupert Blue was honored with
a lavish ceremony

1659
01:46:20.374 --> 01:46:23.756
at the Fairmont Hotel on Nob Hill.

1660
01:46:26.966 --> 01:46:29.313
The dinner was rat-themed.

1661
01:46:29.348 --> 01:46:32.627
They had ice cream molds
in the shape of rat traps.

1662
01:46:32.662 --> 01:46:36.320
They drank wine punch from beakers

1663
01:46:36.355 --> 01:46:38.806
that were shaped like little trash cans.

1664
01:46:38.840 --> 01:46:40.877
It was kind of visual puns everywhere.

1665
01:46:43.017 --> 01:46:46.330
It was a darkly
humorous nod to the rats killed.

1666
01:46:46.365 --> 01:46:49.920
two million in all.
roughly five times the size

1667
01:46:49.955 --> 01:46:51.646
of San Francisco's human population.

1668
01:46:54.269 --> 01:46:57.445
And when he was
called to the dais to accept his gift

1669
01:46:57.480 --> 01:46:58.895
and the city's thanks.

1670
01:46:58.929 --> 01:47:02.070
some of Blue's old shyness came
flooding back and he said.

1671
01:47:02.105 --> 01:47:06.523
"It's difficult to speak
when one's heart is full."

1672
01:47:06.558 --> 01:47:10.596
After all his achievements.
he got rather tongue-tied.

1673
01:47:13.081 --> 01:47:17.361
It was likely Blue's
reticence arose from not just humility.

1674
01:47:17.396 --> 01:47:21.331
but a clear-eyed view of the
debt he owed his predecessor.

1675
01:47:21.365 --> 01:47:24.921
True. he had been able to clean
up San Francisco

1676
01:47:24.955 --> 01:47:28.821
and rid the city of its rats.

1677
01:47:28.856 --> 01:47:30.927
But Kinyoun was the one who insisted

1678
01:47:30.961 --> 01:47:35.656
that the problem even existed.
and at enormous personal cost.

1679
01:47:38.037 --> 01:47:40.626
Blue was seen as a hero.

1680
01:47:40.661 --> 01:47:43.111
and he continued on an upward trajectory.

1681
01:47:43.146 --> 01:47:44.492
You know. he became

1682
01:47:44.527 --> 01:47:47.840
the fourth Surgeon General of
the United States.

1683
01:47:47.875 --> 01:47:50.671
He was a very forward thinker.

1684
01:47:50.705 --> 01:47:52.983
He was somebody who advocated

1685
01:47:53.018 --> 01:47:56.780
for better treatment of the mentally ill.

1686
01:47:56.815 --> 01:47:59.507
He advocated for a national
health insurance at a time

1687
01:47:59.542 --> 01:48:03.062
when that was never heard of whatsoever.

1688
01:48:03.097 --> 01:48:05.893
He saw where the world was going.

1689
01:48:09.621 --> 01:48:14.349
Dr. Joseph Kinyoun's
ouster from San Francisco represented

1690
01:48:14.384 --> 01:48:17.180
a kind of failure of institutional

1691
01:48:17.214 --> 01:48:19.838
resistance and rivalries.

1692
01:48:19.872 --> 01:48:23.807
But he is remembered for bringing

1693
01:48:23.842 --> 01:48:26.810
state of the art methods

1694
01:48:26.845 --> 01:48:31.746
of diagnosing infectious
diseases to America.

1695
01:48:31.781 --> 01:48:34.646
He is remembered for helping found

1696
01:48:34.680 --> 01:48:37.234
the National Hygienic Laboratory.

1697
01:48:37.269 --> 01:48:40.824
the forerunner of our modern
National Institutes of Health.

1698
01:48:40.859 --> 01:48:44.448
for which he is posthumously recognized

1699
01:48:44.483 --> 01:48:47.072
as the first director of NIH.

1700
01:48:50.938 --> 01:48:54.666
The two men brought an end to the epidemic

1701
01:48:54.700 --> 01:48:58.532
using vastly different approaches.

1702
01:48:58.566 --> 01:49:02.363
Yet. it was the efforts of not
just Kinyoun and Blue.

1703
01:49:02.397 --> 01:49:04.676
but the marginalized community

1704
01:49:04.710 --> 01:49:07.679
that still managed to stand up
for its rights.

1705
01:49:07.713 --> 01:49:09.784
that led to a paradigm shift

1706
01:49:09.819 --> 01:49:13.132
in the way America viewed public health.

1707
01:49:18.759 --> 01:49:23.142
One of the things
we learned in San Francisco

1708
01:49:23.177 --> 01:49:26.111
is that intervention into a
disease pandemic

1709
01:49:26.145 --> 01:49:28.009
is a profoundly political act.

1710
01:49:30.115 --> 01:49:34.291
Science is one dimension

1711
01:49:34.326 --> 01:49:39.365
to provide answers and to
provide solutions.

1712
01:49:39.400 --> 01:49:41.333
but it was still subject
to human interpretation.

1713
01:49:41.367 --> 01:49:42.748
human implementation.

1714
01:49:46.234 --> 01:49:49.134
The question that came up in 1900

1715
01:49:49.168 --> 01:49:52.793
is what is the balance between
public necessity.

1716
01:49:52.827 --> 01:49:54.726
public health. and individual
rights and liberties?

1717
01:49:56.693 --> 01:49:58.695
And it was balanced in a terrible way.

1718
01:50:02.388 --> 01:50:06.634
Power-seeking politicians.

1719
01:50:06.669 --> 01:50:10.086
and misguided commercial greed
that takes precedence

1720
01:50:10.120 --> 01:50:13.745
over public health. all of that

1721
01:50:13.779 --> 01:50:18.301
delayed a solution in San Francisco.

1722
01:50:18.335 --> 01:50:21.649
In the end. we needed
collaboration and cooperation

1723
01:50:21.684 --> 01:50:25.204
by the federal.
state. and local governments.

1724
01:50:25.239 --> 01:50:27.862
participation by the citizenry.

1725
01:50:27.897 --> 01:50:32.660
understanding and acceptance of science.

1726
01:50:35.905 --> 01:50:40.461
Science is
implicated with the larger society.

1727
01:50:40.495 --> 01:50:44.154
In San Francisco. we actually
pressed science to do work

1728
01:50:44.189 --> 01:50:46.674
that it has no business doing.

1729
01:50:46.709 --> 01:50:48.469
You don't need science to tell us

1730
01:50:48.503 --> 01:50:51.679
that we should treat people
with dignity and love.

1731
01:50:51.714 --> 01:50:54.268
Science is a method of inquiry.

1732
01:50:54.302 --> 01:50:58.790
It knows a lot.
but there's always unknowns.

1733
01:50:58.824 --> 01:51:03.311
We had some worldviews
that were coming into big conflict

1734
01:51:03.346 --> 01:51:06.245
about how to think about science.

1735
01:51:06.280 --> 01:51:10.664
about how to deal with
a public health crisis.

1736
01:51:10.698 --> 01:51:15.289
how to not ascribe
a racial cause for the disease.

1737
01:51:15.323 --> 01:51:17.705
and diverting accountability.

1738
01:51:17.740 --> 01:51:20.294
But also to think about.

1739
01:51:20.328 --> 01:51:24.436
is it possible to protect myself
from disease?

1740
01:51:24.470 --> 01:51:27.094
Is it possible to eradicate disease?

1741
01:51:27.128 --> 01:51:30.614
And those are open questions.



